            "rendered": "Binay Adhikari, Ph.D."
        },
        "content": {
            "rendered": "<h3><strong>Degrees</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Ph.D. University of Alabama</li>\n<li>M.S. Auburn University</li>\n<li>MBA Kathmandu University, Nepal</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>About</strong></h3>\n<p>Dr. Binay Adhikari earned an MBA from Kathmandu University, Nepal, an M.S. in finance from Auburn University and a Ph.D. in finance from the University of Alabama. He has previously taught at the University of Texas at Rio Grande Valley, Miami University of Ohio, University of Alabama and Kathmandu University. He also worked briefly as a cash supervisor at Standard Chartered Bank in Kathmandu, Nepal.</p>\n<p>He has published in the <em>Journal of Accounting and Economics</em>, <em>Journal of Financial and Quantitative Analysis</em> and <em>Journal of Corporate Finance</em>. His research has been presented at the Financial Intermediation Research Society (FIRS), European Finance Association (EFA), Midwest Finance Association (MFA), China International Conference in Finance (CICF) and Financial Management Association (FMA) among others.</p>\n<h3><strong>Research Interests</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Corporate finance</li>\n<li>Financial markets</li>\n<li>Investments</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Selected Publications</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>“<a href=\"https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D3276309&amp;data=04%7C01%7CWendy.Frost%40utsa.edu%7Ce323c4a1072a4a348f0308d93677198a%7C3a228dfbc64744cb88357b20617fc906%7C0%7C0%7C637600707545623730%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=pG%2BSF1zt%2BTHEF%2FzPcsJWVyFpDuoqfD1cP%2F1%2Bq5oVopM%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Unintended Consequences of the Dodd-Frank Act on Credit Rating Risk and Corporate Finance</a>,” with B. Sharma, A. Agrawal, B. Arthur and M. Rabarison, <em>Journal of Financial and Quantitative Analysis</em>, forthcoming.</li>\n<li>“<a href=\"https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0929119920302704&amp;data=04%7C01%7CWendy.Frost%40utsa.edu%7Ce323c4a1072a4a348f0308d93677198a%7C3a228dfbc64744cb88357b20617fc906%7C0%7C0%7C637600707545623730%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=7ciDq0kL3Xxh%2FZSR2MWLj3K3LotOIz10lmJUsacLpjY%3D&amp;reserved=0\">Shareholder Litigation Rights and Stock Price Crash Risk</a>,” with I. Obaydin, R. Zurbruegg, Md N. Hossain and A. Elnahas, 2021, <em>Journal of Corporate Finance</em>, Vol. 66: 101826.</li>\n<li><span data-contrast=\"none\">&#8220;</span><a href=\"https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=2939135\"><span data-contrast=\"none\">Does Local Capital Supply Matter for Public Firms&#8217; Capital Structures</span></a><span data-contrast=\"none\">?</span><span data-contrast=\"none\">&#8221; </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">with David Cicero and Johan </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">Sulaeman</span><span data-contrast=\"none\">, </span><i><span data-contrast=\"none\">Journal of Financial and Quantitative Analysis</span></i><span data-contrast=\"none\">, forthcoming.</span><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;201341983&quot;:2,&quot;335559740&quot;:408}\"> </span></li>\n<li><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;201341983&quot;:2,&quot;335559740&quot;:408}\"> </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">“</span><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0165410118301095\"><span data-contrast=\"none\">Do Women Managers Keep Firms Out of Trouble? Evidence from Corporate Litigation and Policies</span></a><span data-contrast=\"none\">,”</span><span data-contrast=\"none\">  </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">with </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">Anup</span><span data-contrast=\"none\"> Agrawal and James </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">Malm</span><span data-contrast=\"none\">,  </span><i><span data-contrast=\"none\">Journal of Accounting and Economics</span></i><span data-contrast=\"none\">, Vol. 67, 2019, pp. 202-225. </span></li>\n<li><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;201341983&quot;:2,&quot;335559740&quot;:408}\"> </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">“</span><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0929119917306697\"><span data-contrast=\"none\">Peer Influence on Payout Policies,</span></a><span data-contrast=\"none\">” with </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">Anup</span><span data-contrast=\"none\"> Agrawal, </span><i><span data-contrast=\"none\">Journal of Corporate Finance ,</span></i><i><span data-contrast=\"none\"> </span></i>Vol. <span data-contrast=\"none\">48, 2018, pp. 615-637. </span></li>\n<li><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;201341983&quot;:2,&quot;335559740&quot;:408}\"> </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">“</span><a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0929119916301079\"><span data-contrast=\"none\">Causal Effect of Analyst Following on Corporate Social Responsibility,</span></a><span data-contrast=\"none\">” </span><i><span data-contrast=\"none\">Journal of Corporate Finance,</span></i> Vol<i><span data-contrast=\"none\">. </span></i><span data-contrast=\"none\">41, 2016, pp. 201-216. </span></li>\n<li><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233117&quot;:true,&quot;134233118&quot;:true,&quot;201341983&quot;:2,&quot;335559740&quot;:408}\"> </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">“</span><a href=\"http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=2465052\"><span data-contrast=\"none\">Does Local Religiosity Matter for Bank Risk-Taking</span></a><span data-contrast=\"none\">?</span><a href=\"http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=2465052\"><span data-contrast=\"none\">”</span></a><span data-contrast=\"none\">with </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">Anup</span><span data-contrast=\"none\"> Agrawal, </span><i><span data-contrast=\"none\"> Journal of Corporate Finance , </span></i>Vol. <span data-contrast=\"none\">38, 2016, pp. 272-293. </span></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=2316891\"><span data-contrast=\"none\">“Religion, Gambling Attitudes </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">and Corporate Innovation</span></a><span data-contrast=\"none\">,” </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">with </span><span data-contrast=\"none\">Anup</span><span data-contrast=\"none\"> Agrawal, </span><i><span data-contrast=\"none\">Journal of Corporate Finance, </span></i>Vol.  <span data-contrast=\"none\">37, 2016, pp. 229-248. </span></li>\n</ul>\n",
